</taxonomicName>
is one of the most widespread species in the East Palaearctic and Oriental regions, its distribution ranging from 
<collectingCountry id="EDF67654EF46FFFBFCF2FD9FFCA7FD5B" box="[809,861,618,640]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="458">India</collectingCountry>
to Kamchatka, 
<collectingCountry id="EDF67654EF46FFFBFC26FD9EFBC3FD5B" box="[1021,1081,619,640]" name="Japan" pageId="9" pageNumber="458">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="EDF67654EF46FFFBFF69FD72FEE1FD46" box="[178,283,647,669]" name="Singapore" pageId="9" pageNumber="458">Singapore</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="EDF67654EF46FFFBFE8BFD7DFE7BFD46" box="[336,385,648,669]" name="Laos" pageId="9" pageNumber="458">Laos</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F1704B35EF46FFFBFE54FD72FDD9FD46" author="ASSING V" box="[399,547,647,669]" pageId="9" pageNumber="458" pagination="115 - 190" refId="ref5408" refString="ASSING V. (2012 a): The Rugilus species of the Palaearctic and Oriental regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde A, Neue Serie 5: 115 - 190." type="journal article" year="2012">ASSING 2012a</bibRefCitation>
